<h3>Generator Options</h3>

<ul>
  <li><code>--stimulus</code>: Generates a new Stimulus controller named modal_controller.js and registers it for enhanced interactivity</li>
  <li><code>--directory</code>: Customize the component location (defaults to <code>app/views/rui/components</code>)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Component Properties</h3>

<ul>
  <li><code>title</code>: Modal header title (String, optional)</li>
  <li><code>content</code>: Main modal content as string or block (String or block, required)</li>
  <li><code>size</code>: Modal width size (Symbol, default: :md)
    <ul>
      <li><code>:xs</code>: Extra small modal (max-w-xs)</li>
      <li><code>:sm</code>: Small modal (max-w-sm)</li>
      <li><code>:md</code>: Medium modal (max-w-md)</li>
      <li><code>:lg</code>: Large modal (max-w-lg)</li>
      <li><code>:xl</code>: Extra large modal (max-w-xl)</li>
      <li><code>:full</code>: Full width modal with margins (max-w-full mx-4)</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><code>dismissable</code>: Show close button and allow backdrop dismiss (Boolean, default: true)</li>
  <li><code>classes</code>: Additional CSS classes for modal dialog (String, optional)</li>
  <li><code>backdrop_classes</code>: Additional CSS classes for backdrop overlay (String, optional)</li>
  <li><code>controller</code>: Stimulus controller name (String, default: "railsui-modal")</li>
  <li><code>show</code>: Whether modal is initially visible (Boolean, default: false)</li>
</ul>

